The paper deals with compressive phase retrieval, which is a problem in signal processing and information theory. The use of sparse signals and the numerical experiments with images suggest that the paper could be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SP (Signal Processing). Additionally, the experiments involve image processing, which could place the paper under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of probabilistic algorithms and numerical optimization techniques could also suggest a categorization under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
